# Sanity document IDs (frontend server)

## Rule

Root `_id` containing **`.`** (`caseStudy.co2lab`, `industryPage.medicine`, `countryOption.UA`, …) is a Content Lake **sub-path** → **never** returned to unauthenticated queries.

`sanity-client.ts`: **no token**, `perspective: "published"`, CDN. Do **not** add `SANITY_API_TOKEN` / read token to mask missing docs.

`status == "published"` in GROQ is schema semantics only — not a substitute for public `_id` shape.

## Wrong vs right diagnosis

| Symptom | Wrong fix | Check first |
|--------|-----------|-------------|
| Studio has more docs than site | GROQ `limit`, Releases, “republish all” | Dotted `_id` in admin (`_id match "*.*"`) |
| Token used to “fix” portfolio | Re-add token in prod | Migrate IDs in admin (`reupload:dotted-*`) |

## June 2026

Production migrated to UUIDs in admin. Expect **no** dotted user content IDs. Historical 21 vs 8 cases was pre-migration.

## Code in this repo

- Query by **`slug.current`** for routes — not hard-coded `_id`.
- No dotted `_id` literals in `src/lib/server/*`.

